### 2. Direct Service Access

### Get All Customers (Direct)
GET http://localhost:8081/customers

### Get Customer by ID (Direct)
GET http://localhost:8081/customers/1

### Get All Products (Direct)
GET http://localhost:8082/products

### Get Product by ID (Direct)
GET http://localhost:8082/products/1

### Get All Bills (Direct)
GET http://localhost:8083/bills

### Get Full Bill by ID (Direct)
GET http://localhost:8083/fullBill/1

###
### 3. Gateway Access (Recommended)

### Get All Customers via Gateway
GET http://localhost:9999/customer-service/customers

### Get Customer by ID via Gateway
GET http://localhost:9999/customer-service/customers/1

### Get All Products via Gateway
GET http://localhost:9999/inventory-service/products

### Get Product by ID via Gateway
GET http://localhost:9999/inventory-service/products/1

### Get All Bills via Gateway
GET http://localhost:9999/billing-service/bills

### Get Full Bill via Gateway (with Customer and Product details)
GET http://localhost:9999/billing-service/fullBill/1

###
### 4. Create Operations

### Create New Customer via Gateway
POST http://localhost:9999/customer-service/customers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Eva Laurent",
  "email": "eva@example.com"
}

### Create New Product via Gateway
POST http://localhost:9999/inventory-service/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "AirPods Pro",
  "price": 249.99,
  "quantity": 50
}

###
### 5. Update Operations

### Update Customer via Gateway
PUT http://localhost:9999/customer-service/customers/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Alice Martin (Updated)",
  "email": "alice.updated@example.com"
}

### Update Product via Gateway
PUT http://localhost:9999/inventory-service/products/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Laptop Dell XPS 15 (Updated)",
  "price": 1399.99,
  "quantity": 75
}

